    <text id="F3505T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>This document is an unsigned request for leave for John Ault to recover from his
                    illnesses.</p>
            </div1>

        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
               

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-01-13">January 13th, 1863</date>
                        <name type="place">Camp of 126th Regt. Penn. Vols.</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p>The <hi rend="underline">Rev. John Ault, Chaplain</hi> of the 126th <abbr
                        expan="Regiment 
 Pennsylvania Volunteers">Regt. P.V.</abbr> having applied
                    for a certificate on which to <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>nd an application for leave of
                    absence. I certify that I have carefully examined this officer and find him
                    unable to attend to the duties of his profession on account of a severe attack
                    of Influenza. He also suffers from Rheumatism, is much debilitated and entirely
                    unfit for duty. I further it as my opinion that removal from camp is necessary
                    in order for present permanent activity. He grows weaker daily. I therefore most
                    respectfully urge that he be granted a leave of absence for three weeks as I do
                    not believe that he will be able in a less period to resume the duties of his
                    office.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed/>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
